<page name = "overview">
  <language name = "en">
    <title>Overview</title>
    <content>
      <h1>Strengths</h1>
      <p>
        <h2>Portable</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Runs on Unix and Win32.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <h2>Open</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Free software licensed under the Apache License, v2.0.</li>
          <li>Standard protocols: an open server and open clients.</li>
          <li>Supported by open source JMS providers like ActiveMQ.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <h2>Fast</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Engineered in C for speed and efficiency.</li>
          <li>Built around the AMQP/Fast wire-level protocol.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <h2>Reliable</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Based on standard layers: <a href="http://apr.apache.org/">Apache Portable Runtime</a>, <a href="http://www.sleepcat.com/">Berkeley Database Library</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <h1>Advantages</h1>
      <p>
        <h2>Low cost</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Deploy in any application with no software costs.</li>
          <li>Develop once, run anywhere.</li>
       </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <h2>Non-proprietary</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>No vendor bottleneck.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <h2>Standard</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>One wire-level protocol for all middleware.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </content>
  </language>
</page>
